SCIL dMRI pipeline
==================

Run human pipeline

USAGE

nextflow run main.nf [OPTIONAL_ARGUMENTS] (--input)

DESCRIPTION

    --input=/path/to/[root]             Input folder containing multiple subjects
                                        TractoFlow input or TractoFlow results folder
                                        All the files must contain subject id prefix
                                        (e.g. subj1__t1.nii.gz, subj1__bval, subj1_bvec)

    PROFILES (using -profile option (e.g. -profile use_cuda,fully_reproducible))

    input_qc                            Create QC reports for your raw data
                                        --input structure: TractoFlow input folder

    tractoflow_qc_light                 Create QC reports for your TractoFlow results
                                        Output important steps only
                                        --input structure: TractoFlow results folder

    tractoflow_qc_all                   Create QC reports for your TractoFlow results
                                        Output all steps
                                        --input structure: TractoFlow results folder

    rbx_qc                              Create QC reports for your rbx-flow results
                                        --input structure: for each subject, a folder with all the trk inside
                                        and an anatomy named anat.nii.gz or if bundles come from rbx_flow you
                                        can use tree_for_rbx_qc.sh in combine_flows repository.


Files should be compressed Nifti files (.nii.gz)

NOTES

The intermediate working directory is, by default, set to './work'.
To change it, use the '-w WORK_DIR' argument.

The default config file is pipeline_human/nextflow.config.
Use '-C config_file.config' to specify a non-default configuration file.
The '-C config_file.config' must be inserted after the nextflow call
like 'nextflow -C config_file.config run ...'.
